    <h1>Ludi AI Features Addendum</h1>
    <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong></p>
    <p>
      <strong>Parties:</strong> This Addendum is between Deqo Software Ltd ("Deqo",
      "we", "us") and the Customer ("you", "your"). It forms part of and is subject
      to the terms governing your use of the Ludi platform, including any applicable
      service agreement, data processing agreement, or our standard Terms of Service
      and Privacy Policy.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Purpose and Scope</h2>
    <p>
      1.1 This Addendum sets out the terms that apply when you choose to use
      AI-powered features within Ludi ("AI Features"). These features use large
      language models (LLMs) and related artificial intelligence technologies to
      assist with collaboration, analysis, reporting, and automation in your
      workspace.
    </p>
    <p>1.2 AI Features may include, without limitation:</p>
    <ul role="list">
      <li>grouping, summarising, or analysing board content;</li>
      <li>generating meeting notes or session reports;</li>
      <li>generating content;</li>
      <li>
        detecting patterns, themes, or sentiment across boards, users, or teams;
      </li>
      <li>producing benchmarks, insights, or usage statistics;</li>
      <li>
        generating or configuring boards or templates based on user input; and
      </li>
      <li>
        other experimental or evolving AI-driven functionality intended to
        enhance the product experience.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      1.3 Use of AI Features is entirely optional and available only to
      customers who explicitly opt in.
    </p>
    <p>
      1.4 Deqo may modify, restrict, or withdraw AI Features at any time, at
      its sole discretion.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Data Processing and Sub-Processors</h2>
    <p>
      2.1 When enabled, AI Features may send certain customer data to Deqo's AI
      service providers for processing. The categories of data that may be
      processed include:
    </p>
    <ul role="list">
      <li>
        <strong>Board Content</strong>  content created or generated on a board;
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Person Identifiers</strong>  user name, email address, user ID,
        or profile picture;
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Board Metadata</strong>  board name, creation and update timestamps;
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Team and Company Data</strong>  team and company names, IDs, and
        related metadata.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      2.2 Customers must not upload or include any sensitive or special
      category personal data in AI Features, including but not limited to
      health information, financial account numbers, government-issued
      identifiers, or biometric data. Ludi and its AI providers are not
      designed for such data, and Deqo accepts no responsibility for processing
      or storing it.
    </p>
    <p>
