      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      2.4 Each sub-processor acts solely on Deqo's documented instructions and
      is bound by appropriate contractual safeguards, including the EU Standard
      Contractual Clauses where applicable. Data processed by these services is
      not used for model training.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Customer API Keys</h2>
    <p>
      3.1 Customers may choose to use their own API credentials for one or more
      supported AI providers. When doing so, the customer acts as the data
      controller for all data processed through that API key, and Deqo bears no
      responsibility or liability for that processing. For clarity, any AI
      service accessed through a customer-supplied API key is not considered a
      sub-processor of Deqo.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Pricing and Availability</h2>
    <p>
      4.1 Use of AI Features is subject to pricing, plan and term eligibility
      determined by Deqo from time to time. Current pricing and applicable
      usage limits may be made available on request or published within the
      Ludi platform or related materials. Deqo may modify such pricing, limits,
      or availability at any time. Continued use of AI Features after any
      change constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Liability and Disclaimer</h2>
    <p>
      5.1 AI Features are experimental and provided on an "as is" and "as
      available" basis. Deqo does not guarantee the accuracy, reliability, or
      suitability of any AI-generated outputs. To the extent permitted by law,
      Deqo disclaims all liability arising from or related to the use of AI
      Features, except as expressly required under applicable law.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Duration and Withdrawal</h2>
    <p>
      6.1 This Addendum takes effect when you enable or otherwise opt in to any
      AI Feature, and remains in effect until you disable all AI Features or
      your agreement for use of Ludi ends. You may withdraw from participation
      at any time by notifying Deqo in writing or by disabling the Features in
      your account.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Order of Precedence</h2>
    <p>
      7.1 If any conflict arises between this Addendum and any other agreement
      or policy between you and Deqo, this Addendum will prevail for processing
      carried out under AI Features only.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Changes to this Addendum</h2>
    <p>
      8.1 Deqo may update or modify this Addendum from time to time to reflect
      changes in its AI Features, applicable law, or business practices. The
      revised version will take effect upon posting or notification to the
      Customer, unless a later effective date is specified. Material changes
      will be communicated in advance where reasonably practicable. Continued
      use of any AI Feature after the effective date of an updated Addendum
      constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Acceptance</h2>
    <p>
      9.1 By enabling or using any AI Feature, you confirm that you have read,
      understood, and agree to this Addendum.
    </p>

